    }, {
      "columnQualifier" : "20250626",
      "minutesListened" : 0,
      "reason" : "MOST_DIVERSE_DAY",
      "title" : "The day you turned your queue into a genre buffet",
      "description" : "You stitched together a patchwork of genres from dawn to dusk—indie, synthpop, folk, even a dash of surf rock. “I Really Want to Stay at Your House” and “The Bird Song” circled back for second acts, while Dominic Fike, bôa, and Rosa Walton each left their mark. 94 minutes, 36 tracks, 28 artists—your most diverse day of the year.",
      "filedUnderTags" : "[playlist patchwork, genre sampler]"
